== Athletics == {{main|Athletics at the 1991 All-Africa Games}} Three athletes, two female and one male, won more than one event:
*[[Frankie Fredericks]], Namibia (100 metres and 200 metres) *[[Susan Sirma]], Kenya (1500 metres and 3000 metres) *[[Hanan Ahmed Khaled]], Egypt (shot put and discus throw)
In addition, Nigeria won three of the four [[relay race]]s; 4x100 metres for men and women as well as women's 4x400 metres. No new events were added.
