{{Infobox recurring event | |name=Bristol International Kite Festival |logo= |image= Bristol Kite Festival.jpg |caption= A giant millipede kite at Bristol International Kite Festival |location=[[Ashton Court]], [[Bristol]] |coordinates={{coord|51.4437|-2.64157|display=it}} |years_active=24 |first=1986 |dates=September |genre=[[kite]] |website=[http://www.kite-festival.org.uk/ www.kite-festival.org.uk] }}
The '''Bristol International Kite Festival''', full name Bristol International Festival of Kites & Air Creations, is held annually during September in [[Bristol]], England. It takes place at the [[Ashton Court]] estate, which is owned by [[Politics of Bristol|Bristol City Council]], although it is actually in the district of [[North Somerset]]. Entry is free but there is a charge for car parking. The festival started in 1986 and celebrated its 25th anniversary in 2011.<ref name=evpost2005> {{cite news |url=http://www.lexisnexis.com/uk/nexis/results/docview/docview.do?docLinkInd=true&risb=21_T8083313226&format=GNBFI&sort=BOOLEAN&startDocNo=26&resultsUrlKey=29_T8083313229&cisb=22_T8083313228&treeMax=true&treeWidth=0&csi=169745&docNo=2 |title=The sky's the limit|work=Bristol Evening Post, archived at [[LexisNexis]] |publisher=Bristol News and Media |date=3 September 2005 |accessdate=2009-12-06 |last=Staff writer }} </ref>
In 1991, the festival hosted the World Cup Sport Kite Championship.<ref name=evpost2005/> Organiser and kite designer Martin Lester was inducted into the World Kite Museum hall of fame in 1998.<ref> {{cite web |url=http://kitefestival.com/hall-of-fame/ |title=Hall of Fame |publisher=World Kite Museum |accessdate=2009-12-06 }} </ref> Funding problems have caused difficulties but have been overcome and the festival pulls in crowds of over 30,000.<ref name=evpost2009> {{cite news |url=http://www.lexisnexis.com/uk/nexis/results/docview/docview.do?docLinkInd=true&risb=21_T8083313226&format=GNBFI&sort=BOOLEAN&startDocNo=1&resultsUrlKey=29_T8083313229&cisb=22_T8083313228&treeMax=true&treeWidth=0&csi=166254&docNo=1 |title=Lack of backers could sink Bristol kite festival|work=Bristol Evening Post, archived at [[LexisNexis]] |publisher=Bristol News and Media |date=25 June 2009 |accessdate=2009-12-06 |last=Staff writer }} </ref>
