ard Leese]], American guitarist and producer * 1951 &ndash; [[Richard Thomas (actor)|Richard Thomas]], American actor, director, and producer * 1951 &ndash; [[Stellan Skarsgård]], Swedish actor *[[1952]] &ndash; [[Jean-Marie Dedecker]], Belgian martial artist and politician *[[1953]] &ndash; [[Tim Allen]], American actor, comedian, and producer *[[1954]] &ndash; [[Andrzej Lepper]], Polish politician, [[Deputy Prime Minister of the Republic of Poland]] (d. 2011) * 1954 &ndash; [[Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala]], Nigerian economist and politician, [[Minister of Foreign Affairs (Nigeria)|Minister of Foreign Affairs for Nigeria]] *[[1955]] &ndash; [[Alan Hansen]], Scottish footballer and sportscaster * 1955 &ndash; [[Leah Ward Sears]], German-American lawyer and jurist *[[1956]] &ndash; [[Blair Chapman]], Canadian ice hockey player * 1956 &ndash; [[Sal Paolantonio]], American lieutenant and journalist *[[1957]] &ndash; [[Ron Areshenkoff]], Canadian ice hockey player * 1957 &ndash; [[Roy Cooper]], American lawyer and politician, 75th [[Governor of North Carolina]] * 1957 &ndash; [[Bruce Flowers]], American basketball player * 1957 &ndash; [[Andrzej Morozowski]], Polish journalist and author * 1957 &ndash; [[Dicky Thompson]], American golfer *[[1959]] &ndash; [[Boyko Borissov]], Bulgarian footballer and politician, 50th [[Prime Minister of Bulgaria]] * 1959 &ndash; [[Maurice G. Dantec]], French-born Canadian science fiction writer (d. 2016) * 1959 &ndash; [[Steve Georganas]], Australian politician * 1959 &ndash; [[Klaus Iohannis]], Romanian educator and politician, 5th [[President of Romania]] *[[1960]] &ndash; [[Jacques Rougeau]], Canadian wrestler *[[1961]] &ndash; [[Anders Järryd]], Swedish tennis player *[[1962]] &ndash; [[Davey Hamilton]], American race car driver * 1962 &ndash; [[Glenn Michibata]], Canadian-American tennis player and coach * 1962 &ndash; [[Ally Sheedy]], American actress and author * 1962 &ndash; [[Hannah Storm]], American journalist and author *[[1963]] &ndas