{{Infobox song contest | name = Melodifestivalen | year = 1987 | theme = | logo = | final = 21 February 1987 | presenters = [[Fredrik Belfrage]] | winner = "[[Boogaloo (song)|Fyra Bugg & en Coca Cola]]" by [[Lotta Engberg]] | vote = Juries sorted by age | host = | venue = [[Lisebergshallen]], [[Gothenburg]] | entries = | interval = | opening = }}
'''[[Melodifestivalen]] 1987''' was the selection for the 27th song to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was the 26th time that this system of picking a song had been used. 1502 songs were submitted to [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] for the competition. The final was broadcast on [[SVT1|TV1]] and was not broadcast on radio. The winning song's title was changed to "Boogaloo" for the Eurovision Song Contest as it contained chewing gum brand [[:sv:Bugg (tuggummi)|Bugg]] as well drinks company [[Coca-Cola]] in the title.
